formatDescription: Quicken Interchange Format (QIF) is an open specification and specially formated ASCII fie for reading and writing financial data to media (i.e. files). Although still widely used, QIF is a format older than Open Financial Exchange (OFX).
provenanceCompoundName: Digital Preservation Department / The National Archives
formatProvenance: v.120- New description and notes added as part of PRONOM Research Week 2024. Submitted by Brigham Young University.
